pril 2017 |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n===May===\n* 3 May \u2013 Fox+ is launched by [[Fox Networks Group Asia Pacific|Fox]] as a streaming service.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Yeo |first1=Sonia |url=https://www.todayonline.com/entertainment/fox-launches-streaming-service-singapore |title=Fox launches streaming service in Singapore |website=Today |date=3 May 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n* 4 May \u2013 A fire breaks out in a building at Toh Guan, causing 1 fatality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/woman-54-dies-after-fire-breaks-out-in-building-opposite-imm-in-jurong-east|title=Woman, 54, dies after fire breaks out in building opposite IMM in Jurong East|date=2017-05-04|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref> Subsequent investigations by the [[Singapore Civil Defence Force]] found that the building's [[cladding (construction)|cladding]] is flammable and 39 buildings used similar cladding. As a result, 3 cladding brands are found to be unsafe.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/36-buildings-may-have-combustible-cladding-that-doesn-t-meet-9153588|title=36 buildings may have combustible cladding that doesn't meet safety standards; police investigating|date=2017-08-24|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/parliament/37-buildings-identified-with-unsafe-cladding-removal-required-by-9205594|title=37 buildings identified with unsafe cladding; removal required by end-October|date=2017-09-11|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/unsafe-cladding-removed-from-17-buildings-2-more-non-compliant-9481450|title=Unsafe cladding removed from 17 buildings, 2 more non-compliant cladding models identified|date=2017-12-08|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref>\n* 8 May \u2013 A debate on milk prices ensued in Parliament after The Straits Times reported in March that milk prices more than doubled over the past decade.<ref>{{cite web |title=Milk powder price woes: Average cost up by 120% in 10 years |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/milk-powder-price-woes |website=The Straits Times |date=24 March 2017 |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Govt moving to ensure formula milk prices are kept in check |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-guidelines-boost-competitiveness-infant-formula-market |website=Today |date=8 May 2017 |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> Two days later, the [[Competition Commission of Singapore]] found that brand loyalty and demand for premium brands drove milk power prices up.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cccs.gov.sg/media-and-consultation/newsroom/media-releases/formula-milk-market-inquiry-findings |title=CCS\u2019s Findings From the Market Inquiry into the Supply of Formula Milk |website=CCS (now CCCS) |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=10 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Koh |first1=Valerie |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/firms-capitalised-parents-brand-loyalty-penchant-premium-formula-milk-report |title=Milk brands use premium image, consumer behaviour to drive prices up: CCS |website=Today |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=10 May 2017}}</ref> In response, the [[Agri-Food and Veterinary Authority of Singapore]] announced new advertising guidelines that disallows nutrition and health claims, coupled with attractive images, and encourage breastfeeding.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abu Baker |first1=Jalelah |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/nutrition-and-health-claims-to-be-prohibited-on-formula-milk-ava-8832674 |title=Nutrition and health claims to be prohibited on formula milk: AVA |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=10 May 2017}}</ref> In addition, various supermarket chains have introduced affordable milk brands, which are Einmilk (a made-in-Singapore milk brand),<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tay |first1=Tiffany Fumiko |title=Made-in-Singapore infant milk powder launched, costs under $40 for 800g tin |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/made-in-singapore-infant-milk-powder-launched-costs-under-40-for-800g-tin |accessdate=10 August 2019 |website=The Straits Times |date=30 May 2017}}</ref> Australia's Own,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tay |first1=Tiffany Fumiko |title=FairPrice launches Australian milk formula range priced under $35 for a 900g tin |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/fairprice-launches-australian-milk-formula-range-priced-under-35-for-a-900g-tin |accessdate=10 August 2019 |website=The Straits Times |date=15 June 2017}}</ref> Nature One,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ang |first1=Idlyko |title=Sheng Siong launches affordable infant formula from Australia |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/sheng-siong-launches-new-australian-formula-milk-range |accessdate=10 August 2019 |website=Today |date=24 August 2017}}</ref> [[NTUC FairPrice|FairPrice Gold]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kok |first1=Xing Hui |title=NTUC FairPrice launches house brand formula milk, prices start from $27 for 900g tin |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/ntuc-fairprice-launches-house-brand-formula-milk |accessdate=10 August 2019 |website=The Straits Times |date=20 September 2017}}</ref> and [[Blackmores]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Blackmores launches formula milk product in Singapore |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/blackmores-launches-formula-milk-product-in-singapore-9401554 |accessdate=10 August 2019 |website=Channel NewsAsia |date=13 November 2017}}</ref>\n* 12 May \u2013 [[National University of Singapore]] (NUS) and [[Nanyang Technological University]] (NTU) suffered a [[cyberattack]] on their servers.<ref>{{cite web |title=NUS, NTU hit by cyber-attacks targeting Govt info, research data |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/nus-ntu-hit-sophisticated-cyber-attacks |publisher=Todayonline |date=12 May 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}<