w attractions as well as an elevated walkway by 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-attractions-sentosa-2021|title=Sentosa to get new walkway, attraction, more night events|date=2017-06-13|website=Todayonline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref>\n* 18 June \u2013 The Tuas West Extension of the [[East West MRT Line]] opens.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chew |first1=Hui Min |title=4 MRT stations on Tuas West Extension to open on June 18 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/4-mrt-stations-on-tuas-west-extension-to-open-on-june-18 |publisher=The Straits Times |accessdate=6 September 2019 |date=27 April 2017}}</ref>\n* 27 June \u2013 \n**The [[Monetary Authority of Singapore]] will now allow banks to operate or acquire stakes in digital platforms and sell consumer goods and services online. Requirements will also be streamlined for acquisition of complementary non-financial services. However, banks will still not be allowed to venture into property and resort businesses.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mas.gov.sg/news/media-releases/2017/mas-streamlines-framework-for-banks-carrying-on-permissible-non-financial-businesses |title=MAS Streamlines Framework for Banks Carrying On Permissible Non-financial Businesses |website=MAS |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Yahya |first1=Yasmine |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/banking/singapore-banks-must-innovate-will-be-allowed-to-operate-or-own-consumer-goods-and |title=Singapore banks must innovate; will be allowed to operate or own consumer goods and services online businesses, says Heng Swee Keat |website=The Straits Times |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n**At the same time, PayNow is unveiled as a funds transfer service requiring only a mobile or [[National Registration Identity Card|NRIC]] number.<ref name=\"PayNow\">{{Cite web |last1=Lee |first1=Xin En |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/abs-unveils-new-funds-transfer-facility-that-will-require-only-mobile-number-nric |title=ABS unveils new funds transfer facility PayNow which requires only cellphone or identity card number |website=The Straits Times |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n* 29 June \u2013 Singapore's 4th desalination plant, the [[Marina East Desalination Plant]] starts construction. It will have a rooftop garden and a visitors' centre, with completion by 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Lin |first1=Yangchen |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/environment/singapores-fourth-desalination-plant-in-marina-east-will-have-areas-that-are |title=Singapore's 4th desalination plant in Marina East will have areas that are open for visitors |website=The Straits Times |access-date=6 June 2019 |date=29 June 2017}}</ref>\n* 30 June \u2013 Food & beverage outlets will no longer be allowed to apply for new smoking corners, and a [[smoking ban]] in [[Orchard Road]] will take effect on 1 July 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Choo |first1=Felicia |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/environment/fb-outlets-can-no-longer-apply-for-smoking-corners-public-areas-in-orchard |title=F&B outlets can no longer apply for new smoking corners; public areas in Orchard Road to go smoke-free from July 2018 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=5 July 2019 |date=30 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===July===\n* 1 July \u2013 A cycling network is launched in [[Jurong]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/cycling-path-network-that-connects-jurong-east-chinese-garden-and-lakeside-unveiled|title=Cycling path network that connects Jurong East, Chinese Garden and Lakeside unveiled|date=2017-07-01|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref>\n* 3 July \u2013 [[Prime Minister of Singapore|Prime Minister]] [[Lee Hsien Loong]] convenes a two-day special Parliamentary session to debate the accusations of abuse of power made by his siblings in the [[38 Oxley Road]] dispute.<ref>{