will be expanded to accommodate the relocation of [[Paya Lebar Air Base]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/tengah-air-base-to-be-expanded-more-than-80000-graves-exhumed-four-farms-to-be|title=Tengah Air Base to be expanded; more than 80,000 graves exhumed, 4 farms to be acquired|date=18 July 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=4 May 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n* 22 July \u2013 Comic writer [[Sonny Liew]] wins 3 [[Eisner Award]]s for [[The Art of Charlie Chan Hock Chye]],<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Ho |first1=Olivia |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/graphic-novelist-sonny-liew-becomes-first-singaporean-to-win-eisner-award |title=Graphic novelist Sonny Liew is first Singaporean to win Eisner award, bagging 3 comics Oscars |website=The Straits Times |access-date=6 May 2019 |date=22 July 2017}}</ref> 2 years after the [[National Arts Council, Singapore|National Arts Council]] (NAC) withdrew funding for his book.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/national-arts-council-revokes-grant-for-graphic-novel-Sonny-Liew |title=NAC withdraws grant for graphic novel publisher due to \"sensitive content\" |website=Today |date=29 May 2015 |access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Charissa |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/nac-pulled-grant-from-comic-as-it-potentially-undermines-the-authority-of-the-government |title=NAC pulled grant from comic as it 'potentially undermines the authority of the Government' |website=The Straits Times |date=3 June 2015 |access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n* 25 July - [[Tigerair]] completes its merger with [[Scoot]], creating a large [[low cost carrier]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Siong |first1=Olivia |title=Tigerair to operate under Scoot brand from July |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/tigerair-to-operate-under-scoot-brand-from-july-8948362 |website=Channel NewsAsia |date=15 June 2017 |accessdate=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* 27 July \u