7}}</ref>\n**[[2017 Singaporean presidential election|2017 Presidential Election]]: former [[Speaker of Parliament (Singapore)|Speaker]] [[Halimah Yacob]] is announced by the Presidential Elections Commission as the only candidate issued with both the certificate of eligibility and community certificate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/halimah-yacob-only-one-to-get-eligibility-certificate-set-to-be-singapores-next-president|title=Halimah Yacob only one to get eligibility certificate, set to be Singapore's next President|last=Yong|first=Charissa|date=11 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=14 September 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n* 13 September \u2013 \n** Two ships collide near Singapore waters, causing two casualties and seven injured, with another three missing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/two-ships-collide-in-singapore-waters-five-crew-members-missing|title=Two ships collide in Singapore waters; 7 injured, 2 dead, 3 missing|last=Lai|first=Linette|date=14 September 2017|work=The Straits Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190125020540/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/two-ships-collide-in-singapore-waters-five-crew-members-missing|archive-date=25 January 2019|url-status=live|last2=Seow|first2=Bei Yi|language=en|last3=Au-Yong|first3=Rachel|access-date=6 April 2019|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n** Nomination day for the [[2017 Singaporean presidential election|2017 Presidential Election]]: former [[Speaker of Parliament (Singapore)|Speaker]] Halimah Yacob won the election via an [[walkover|uncontested walkover]] since she was the only candidate eligible to contest in an election (the third such walkover after [[1999 Singaporean presidential election|1999]] and [[2005 Singaporean presidential election|2005]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesstimes.com.sg/government-economy/presidential-election-2017/halimah-yacob-declared-president-elect-after-walkover|title=Halimah Yacob declared preside