gapore/woodlands-checkpoint-get-new-wing-meet-growing-traffic-needs |publisher=Todayonline |date=30 March 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n* 31 March \u2013 \n**[[Samudera LRT station]] is opened.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sbstransit.com.sg/press/2017-03-20-01.aspx | title=Opening of Samudera Station on Punggol West LRT Loop | publisher=SBS Transit | date=20 March 2017}}</ref>\n**The [[Singapore Botanic Gardens|Botanic Gardens']] new Learning Forest opens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-learning-forest-opens-singapore-botanic-gardens|title=Century-old forest at Botanic Gardens opens|publisher=Todayonline|date=31 March 2017|accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===April===\n* 1 April \u2013 \n**The [[2G]] network ceases with the shutdown completed on 18 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imda.gov.sg/about/newsroom/media-releases/2017/2g-services-to-cease-on-1-april-2017|title=2G Services to Cease on 1 April 2017|website=Info-communications Media Development Authority|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810092035/https://www.imda.gov.sg/about/newsroom/media-releases/2017/2g-services-to-cease-on-1-april-2017|archive-date=10 August 2017|url-status=live|access-date=10 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Lester |title=2G mobile network to shut down from April 1: IMDA reminds users to switch to 3G or 4G |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/tech/2g-mobile-network-to-shut-down-from-april-1-imda-reminds-users-to-switch-to-3g-or-4g |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=17 April 2020 |date=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n**The [[Singapore Art Museum]] will undergo enhancement works, which will finish in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-art-museum-to-get-s-90-million-facelift-8709154|title=Singapore Art Museum to get S$90 million facelift|date=2017-04-01|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref>\n* 2 April \u2013 \n**[[Strollers]] are now allowed on buses in a bid to be family-friendly.<ref>{{cite web |title=Using open strollers on public buses: The dos and don'ts |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/using-open-strollers-on-public-buses-the-dos-and-donts |publisher=The Straits Times |date=8 March 2017 |accessdate=27 June 2019}}</ref>\n**A new vehicle underpass linking the [[Kallang\u2013Paya Lebar Expressway]] and [[Nicoll Highway]] opens to traffic.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lim |first1=Adrian |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/new-vehicular-underpass-linking-kpe-to-nicoll-highway-to-open-on-april-2 |title=New vehicular underpass linking KPE to Nicoll Highway to open on April 2 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=14 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/new-underpass-opens-at-junction-of-nicoll-highway-and-sims-way-8707536 |title=New underpass opens at junction of Nicoll Highway and Sims Way |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=2 April 2017}}</ref>\n* 7 April \u2013 [[City Harvest Church Criminal Breach of Trust Case]]: An appeal regarding the conviction last year concluded; the sentences of the six accused church pastors of [[City Harvest Church]] were shortened.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/city-harvest-appeal-kong-hee-s-sentence-reduced-to-3-5-years-8717606|title=City Harvest appeal: Kong Hee's sentence reduced to 3.5 years|website=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2018-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705233039/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/city-harvest-appeal-kong-hee-s-sentence-reduced-to-3-5-years-8717606|archive-date=2018-07-05|url-status=live}}</ref> All the convicted pastors (with the exception of Chew Eng Han who was on bail; Chew later served his sentence on 22 February 2018) began their jail sentences on 21 April.\n* 9 April \u2013 [[United Overseas Bank]] and [[OCBC Bank]] announced that fees for their shared ATM