ank]] is officially launched in [[KK Women's and Children's Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kotwani |first1=Monica |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-launches-first-donor-breast-milk-bank-9130360 |title=Singapore launches first donor breast milk bank |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=9 November 2019 |date=17 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 20 August \u2013 \n**Singapore beat Malaysia 17-4 to win its 27th SEA Games gold medal in men's water polo. This is the country's longest winning streak in the sport.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/sea-games-mens-water-polo-slideshow-wp-053606658.html|title=SEA Games: Men's water polo team earn 27th gold medal in dominant fashion|last=Chin|first=Nigel|date=20 August 2017|work=Yahoo News Singapore|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824140137/https://sg.news.yahoo.com/sea-games-mens-water-polo-slideshow-wp-053606658.html|archive-date=24 August 2017|url-status=live|language=en-SG|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n**Several new plans are unveiled. There will be 40,000 more pre-school places by 2022, with new Early Years Centres (EYCs) for children up to 4 years old, leading to MOE Kindergartens catering to children aged 5 and 6. The [[Ministry of Education (Singapore)|Ministry of Education]] will set up 50 kindergartens by 2023 compared to 15 now. In addition, a National Institute of Early Childhood Development will be set up under the [[National Institute of Education]] to raise pre-school teachers' standards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goy |first1=Priscilla |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/national-day-rally-2017-more-childcare-places-and-moe-kindergartens-new-institute-for-pre |title=National Day Rally 2017: More childcare places and MOE kindergartens; new institute for pre-school teachers |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> In addition, bilingual education will be emphasised at a young age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Charissa |url=htt