b]], [[NETS (company)|NETS]], [[Razer Inc.|Razer]], among other companies have announced plans to set up cashless systems.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ride-hailing app Grab launches e-payment and fund transfer system |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/tech/ride-hailing-app-grab-launches-e-payment-and-fund-transfer-system |website=The Straits Times |date=30 August 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NETSpay\">{{cite web |title=New app lets users pay by Nets \u2013 using their phones |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/new-app-lets-users-pay-by-nets-using-their-phones |website=The Straits Times |date=20 October 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Razer submits proposal for unified e-payment system |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/tech/razer-submits-proposal-for-unified-e-payment-system |website=The Straits Times |date=7 September 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref> \n* 24 August \u2013 The [[Singapore Tourism Board]] and [[Economic Development Board]] launch the ''[[Passion Made Possible]]'' campaign replacing ''YourSingapore'', used since 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.stb.gov.sg/content/stb/en/media-centre/media-releases/stb-and-singapore-economic-development-board-launch-passion-made-possible-brand-for-singapore.html |title=Singapore Tourism Board and Singapore Economic Development Board launch Passion Made Possible Brand for Singapore |website=STB, EDB |access-date=9 November 2019 |date=24 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kok |first1=Xing Hui |last2=Leow |first2=Annabeth |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapores-new-international-brand-by-stb-and-edb-passion-made-possible |title=Singapore's new international brand by STB and EDB: Passion Made Possible |website=The Straits Times |access-date=9 November 2019 |date=24 August 2017}}</ref>\n* 25 August \u2013 \n**A masterplan for Jurong Lake District is released by the [[Urban Redevelopment Authority]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.co