s-private-hire-cars |title=Smoking ban expanded to outdoor areas in university compounds, private-hire cars |website=The Straits Times |access-date=5 July 2019 |date=26 September 2017}}</ref>\n**Parking.sg is launched, initially open to car users.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/parking-sg-app-to-be-available-from-oct-1-9261962 |title=Parking.sg app to be available from Oct 1 |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=9 November 2019 |date=29 September 2017}}</ref>\n* 2 October \u2013 The Infrastructure Protection Act is passed to provide important buildings with adequate security measures during planning stages.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Koh |first1=Valerie |last2=Cheng |first2=Kenneth |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/infrastructure-protection-bill-passed-parliament |title=Infrastructure Protection Bill passed in Parliament |website=Today |access-date=5 June 2019 |date=2 October 2017}}</ref>\n* 5 October \u2013 The [[Land Transport Authority]] signs an agreement with all five bike-sharing companies (GBikes, Mobike, oBike, ofo and SG Bike), [[National Parks Board|NParks]] and all 16 Town Councils to deal with inconveniences caused by irresponsible bike-sharing users. They will also be required to adopt [[geo-fence|geofencing]] technologies by end-2017.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abdullah |first1=Zhaki |title=LTA signs agreement with bike-sharing firms and stakeholders on responsible parking, riding |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/lta-signs-agreement-with-bike-sharing-firms-nparks-town-councils-on-responsible |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=10 August 2019 |date=5 October 2017}}</ref>\n* 7 October \u2013 A major disruption of train services between Ang Mo Kio and Newton lasted 21 hours due to the [[Bishan tunnel flooding|flooding]] occurred in the MRT tunnels of the North South Line due to a malfunctioned pump.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/flooded-mrt-tunnel-trackside-fire-caused-train-disruption-on-nsl-9289414 |title=Flooded MRT tunnel, trackside fire caused train disruption on NSL: SMRT |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=21 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171015150830/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/flooded-mrt-tunnel-trackside-fire-caused-train-disruption-on-nsl-9289414 |archive-date=15 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Sin |first1=Yuen |url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/problem-with-water-pumps-behind-mrt-disruption |title=Problem with water pumps behind North-South Line disruption over weekend |website=The Straits Times |access-date=21 October 2017 |date=9 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021183843/http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/problem-with-water-pumps-behind-mrt-disruption |archive-date=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n* 8 October - Singaporean singer [[Joanna Dong]] finishes third in [[Sing! China (season 2)]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Singh |first1=Bryna |title=Singaporean singer Joanna Dong emerges second runner-up in Sing! China finals |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/singaporean-singer-joanna-dong-is-out-of-grand-finals-of-sing-china |website=The Straits Times |access-date=29 September 2019 |date=8 October 2017}}</ref>\n* 9 October \u2013 [[Singapore Post|SingPost]] Centre reopens with after two years of retrofitting works.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.singpost.com/about-us/news-releases/singpost-centre-new-one-stop-lifestyle-destination-singapore\u2019s-east-launched-today |title=SingPost Centre, the new one-stop lifestyle destination in Singapore's east is launched today |website=SingPost |access-date=20 April 2019 |date=9 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singpost-centre-shopping-mall-reopens-with-retail-space-doubled-9292432 |title=SingPost Centre shopping mall reopens with retail space doubled |website=Channel NewsAsia |access-date=20 April 2019 |dat